explanation: The solution uses a string to store the text and an integer to keep track of the cursor position. The addText function inserts the text at the cursor position and updates the cursor. The deleteText function erases the characters to the left of the cursor and updates the cursor. The cursorLeft and cursorRight functions update the cursor position and return the last min(10, len) characters to the left of the cursor.

